review_blob: Disappointed.  Pours with bubbles similar to a bottle of coke with a head that disappears faster than a coke. Even tastes like a sour version of coke.  Very thin in body. Not smooth on the palate like most porters Ive tried.
This beer is definatly pleasing to drink.  However, its not as strong as I would have liked.  It has a good feel.  Almost as smooth as a glass of milk.

As much as I hate this beer.
I love it. Because no night in college would have been right without throwing a few of these back.

beer_brewer_name: Wild Goose Brewery (Frederick Brewing Company/Flying Dog)
review_blob: At 21 Im a newbie to the world of beer tasting, but Ive become infatuated with stouts.  Wild Goose has a rich flavor and smooth after taste.  This is definatly worth a try.
